Overview This program is a fun and "silly" terminal pet game,
throwback to the 90's kids, where the user takes care of a tiny “server pet.”
Each turn the user chooses an action (like feeding coffee or applying patches) that affects
the pet’s stats.
The game ends when the pet’s health reaches zero or the user survives all turns.
Product Backlog: Here are the features I hope to create in order, as time permits.
Provide a short welcome message and explain how to play
Create starting stats for the server pet (ex: health, energy, mood)
Show a menu of actions each turn and ask the user to choose one
Update stats based on the user’s choice and display the new stats
Add a small “time passing” effect each turn (ex: health/energy slowly decrease)
Add random events that change stats (printer demon, phishing click, etc.)
End the game with a win/lose message depending on final health

START PROGRAM

PRINT welcome message + instructions

SET health = 10
SET energy = 8
SET mood = 5        # optional stat, can be flavor only
SET turn = 1
SET max_turns = 10

WHILE turn <= max_turns AND health > 0:

    PRINT "---- Turn", turn, "----"
    PRINT current stats (health, energy, mood)

    PRINT menu of actions:
        1) Feed coffee
        2) Apply patches
        3) Restart service
        4) Ignore alerts

    GET user choice

    IF choice == 1:
        energy = energy + 3
        mood = mood + 1
        PRINT outcome text
    ELSE IF choice == 2:
        health = health + 3
        energy = energy - 2
        PRINT outcome text
    ELSE IF choice == 3:
        health = health + 2
        energy = energy - 1
        PRINT outcome text
    ELSE IF choice == 4:
        energy = energy + 1
        health = health - 3
        mood = mood - 1
        PRINT outcome text
    ELSE:
        PRINT "Invalid choice, try again"
        # (optional: do not change stats)

    # time passing effect each turn
    health = health - 1
    energy = energy - 1

    # random event (optional backlog item)
    RANDOMLY decide if event happens (ex 20% chance)
    IF event happens:
        PICK one random event from list
        APPLY event effect to stats
        PRINT event text

    CLAMP stats so they don’t go below 0 (optional but nice):
        IF health < 0: health = 0
        IF energy < 0: energy = 0
        IF mood < 0: mood = 0

    turn = turn + 1

END WHILE

IF health <= 0:
    PRINT lose message
ELSE:
    PRINT win message

END PROGRAM


